Key Match Events: Yoshinobu Yamamoto allowed four runs in three innings, marking only the third time he failed to see north of four innings across 17 starts in 2024.
Mookie Betts hit his 19th home run of the campaign in walk-off fashion.
Shohei Ohtani hit another home run and collected two stolen bases, inching closer to the 60-60 club with 53 home runs and 55 stolen bases.
Post-Match Reflections: The Dodgers can expect to be carried by Shohei Ohtani in the postseason.
The Dodgers hope that third baseman Max Muncy will quickly recover from upper body soreness and that support for their injured pitching staff will deliver when needed.
